President Obama and Vice President Biden announced details about programs for middle-class families during a meeting of the Middle Class Task Force. The programs aim to alleviate the financial burden on middle-class families and provide assistance in areas such as child care, elder care, student loans, retirement savings, and support for working families. The recommendations include increasing the child and dependent care tax credit for middle-class families, limiting federal student loan payments to 10% of income, creating an automatic IRA enrollment system, increasing tax credits for retirement savings, and providing support for families balancing work and elder care responsibilities. The final report and recommendations from the Middle Class Task Force will be released in February.